
[1]concentrate

   CONCENTRATE, v.t. [See Concenter.]

   1. To bring to a common center, or to a closer union; to cause to
   approach nearer to a point, or center; to bring nearer to each other;
   as, to concentrate particles of salt by evaporating the water that
   holds them in solution; to concentrate the troops in an army; to
   concentrate rays of light into a focus.

   2. To increase the specific gravity of a body.
